The paper deals with the problem of efficiently locating the most recent copy of a pattern in an online stream, which is a common problem in data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of suffix trees and the optimization of Ukkonen's algorithm also suggest a focus on string algorithms and data compression (cs.DM). The paper also mentions sliding-window indexing, which is a technique used in distributed computing and parallel algorithms (cs.CC). Finally, the use of logarithmic factors and optimization techniques suggests a focus on algorithm analysis and optimization (cs.LG).
